Package: Oregon7Q10
Title: Calculation of 7Q10 flow for gauging stations in Oregon
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Dan", "Sobota", email = "sobota.daniel@deq.state.or.us", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: This function returns the lowest seven-day average discharge expected once every 10 years based on a continuous record of data.  The 7Q10 can reflect an annual, seasonal, or monthly statistic. Methods are consistent with the EPA's DFLOW methods.  Also included is a function, OWRD_stations, that links you to the Oregon Water Resources website to browse station IDs.
Depends: R (>= 3.4.3)
License: GNU General Public License v3.0
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Imports: PearsonDS,
         dplyr,
         zoo,
         magrittr,
         purrr,
         moments
